edu.unm.health.biocomp.hscaf

Class ScaffoldStore

  • Object
    • ScaffoldStore

  • public class ScaffoldStore
extends Object
    Initiate and provide local storage & retrieval via BerkeleyDB. For large jobs this avoids memory limits and improves performance by storing solved scaffolds for rapid lookup and avoiding re-calculation.
    Note that ScaffoldSet is an alternative for in-memory storage, for if BerkeleyDB is unavailable or for small datasets.
    For largest jobs use ScaffoldDB (PostgreSQL).
    Author:
    Jeremy J Yang

      String getScaffoldString(ScaffoldEntity scent)
      Generates string representing the hierarchical scaffold sub tree rooted by this scaffold. Same format as Scaffold.subTreeAsString(). e.g. "1:(2,3)" or "1:(2:(3,4,5),6:(4,7))"
      String getStatsString()
      Returns BerkeleyDB environment stats.
      String info(int verbose)
      Returns information about contents of ScaffoldStore and underlying BerkeleyDB database and environment.
      Boolean isKeep_nitro_attachments()
      Is keep_nitro_attachments flag on for scaffolds in this ScaffoldStore.
      Boolean isStereo()
      Is stereo flag on for scaffolds in this ScaffoldStore.
      int mergeScaffoldTree(Scaffold scaf)
      Merges a fully populated ScaffoldTree defined by the Scaffold argument with the ScaffoldStore. New scaffolds are assigned new IDs. Existing scaffolds are recognized as such. Initially called with new root scaffold, then recursively. For each call, process all immediate child scaffolds, then assign ChildIds and ParentId to ScaffoldEntity. Note that a new unknown parent may have known and/or new child scaffolds. Hence this recursive method must handle the known-scaffold case.
      int populateScaffoldTree(Scaffold scaf)
      Populates an incomplete ScaffoldTree from known root Scaffold. Note that since root scaffold is known, all child scaffolds must also be known. For known scaffold, obtain ID from store, and find child scaffolds in store to populate ScaffoldTree.
      void removeAll()
      Delete all data from scaffold databases.
